spirit:component.spirit:name: ibert_ultrascale_gty_0
spirit:component.spirit:description: The IBERT Ultrascale GTY core is customizable and designed for evaluating and monitoring Ultrascale FPGA GTY transceivers. This core includes pattern generators and checkers that are implemented in FPGA logic, and access to ports and the dynamic reconfiguration port attributes of the GTY transceivers. Communication logic is also included to allow the design to be run-time accessible through Joint Test Action Group (JTAG). Run-time interaction with this core requires the use of the Vivado serial I/O analyzer feature.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: INS_LOSS_NYQ_1

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_EQ_MODE_1
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Specify the equalization mode, or allow the core to select a mode. Refer to the product guide for guidelines on selecting between DFE and LPM modes.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_COUPLING_1
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the link coupling

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_TERMINATION_1
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the receiver termination

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_TERMINATION_PROG_VALUE_1
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the termination voltage (in mV) when in programmable mode

spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: PPM offset between receiver and transmitter
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Specify the PPM offset between received data and transmitted data

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: RX_SSC_PPM_1
